profile_positions.description:
Responsibilities and management control tasks:

 Leading a donor compliance and control project team since March 2014 that develops tools, formats, procedures, and new contract forms on subjects like audit methodologies, revenue models through transfer pricing and tariff setting, financial contract management, procurement, treasury, MIS & management contracts, and database management;
 Advise HQ departments, EB and regional/ country offices with regard to implementing measurements for donor compliance, setting up a donor compliant administration, accounting and all other financial aspects related to technical requirements of donors;
 Manage the going concern of various accounts like Albert Heijn Foundation and IDH (the sustainable trade initiative);
 Coach/ train finance and administration managers, financial officers and bookkeepers and organize workshops on financial requirements and obligations of back donors in the HQ and in regional/ country offices;
 Business control on financial reports and audit reports of high risk and key partners and monitor partners’ financial position and policy;
 Identify and inform implementing partners and colleagues about compliance risks and advise them on necessary changes;
 Assess and monitor cross-region and country budgeting, reporting & reconciliation and identify cash depletion;

Responsibilities and tasks:

 Analyze and assess program and project proposals including revenues, spending, investment analysis and cash flow forecasts;
 Monitor and evaluate partner organizations, programs and projects by analysis of financial reports and audits;
 Coach/ train finance and administration managers, financial officers and bookkeepers and organize workshops on financial requirements and obligations of back donors in Humanitarian Assistance programs;

Responsibilities and tasks:

 Responsible for financial analysis, assessment and monitoring of the Pakistan program and project proposals and contracts, the evaluation and capacity building of the partner organizations, and the preparation and review of plans, budgets, performance reports, and resources management audits (RMA’s);
 Depleted a total budget of around 2,4 million Euros raised out of different fund sources of which most funds had to be implemented in 1 year (SHO funds);
 Recruited I&K country representative in Pakistan and set up two office arrangements. Decisively involved in the appointing of the monitoring officer in the Pakistan country office;
 Conducted regularly field visits to project areas in Pakistan;
 Organized a Round Table Meeting in December 2010 for our I&K partners involved in the flood relief work to streamline the relief work and regular development work, share amongst each other the good and bad experiences and plan out the way forward;
 Contributed to establishing an integrated disaster and development program in Pakistan for further fund raising;
 Organized a safety and security training in Islamabad for local Ngo’s in Pakistan.

Responsibilities and tasks:

 Represent I&K within all relevant development networks of national and international Ngo’s, and within government platforms in Nepal.
 Develop and maintain both internal and external relationships to ensure program growth and optimum program success;
 Coordinate and manage overall country/program budgets within approved spending levels and ensure compliance with all I&K rules and regulations;
 Coordinate overall country budget; manage budget within approved spending levels and establish an annual cash flow plan to ensure a steady and adequate supply of funds for program activities; oversee budget management of sub-grantees/sub-contractors;
 Ensure adherence to operational imperatives as per internal/ external audit requirements;
 Develop and implement the HR manual in Nepal, appointing new staff members;
 Ensure accurate and timely financial reporting to I&K regional office/ regional manager and global office;
 Manage security and safety of the country team and I&K assets according to best practices, I&K operating standards and field realities; ensure an up-to-date I&K country security plan is in place and fully understood by all team members including evacuation plans; liaise with the Global Security Advisor, and Regional Manager on crucial events, high risk periods, incident reporting or security policy changes;
 Organize workshops and capacity building trajectories on financial management and safety and security training in order to enhance the capacity and security of the implementing partners of I&K.

I was assigned by the faculty of Health, Department of Nursing as project and administration officer.  
Examples of my duties were:

      Setting up of financial administration system: budgeting, monitoring & reporting systems;
	Perform cost prize calculations of educational courses;
	Writing on the marketing plan for department of Nursing;
	Innovate quality & control measurements continuously;
	IT database engineering continuously;
	Restructuring of front- and back office;
	Coordination of websites of educations & courses
